---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Research — Aryan D Haritsa">

  <!-- Page Header -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-grid bg-grid-fade opacity-40 pointer-events-none"></div>
    <div class="container-wide pt-20 pb-14 relative">
      <p class="eyebrow reveal mb-5">Ongoing work</p>
      <h1 class="reveal text-5xl md:text-7xl font-light tracking-[-0.035em] leading-[0.95] mb-6" style="font-family: var(--font-serif); color: var(--color-accent);">
        Research.
      </h1>
      <p class="reveal text-[var(--color-muted)] leading-relaxed max-w-[640px] text-lg">
        Two active threads investigating the internal mechanisms of neural networks and how architectural choices shape model behavior — plus paper work in progress.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="container-prose"><div class="h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-[var(--color-accent)]/20 to-transparent"></div></div>

  <!-- ============ ORPHEUS ============ -->
  <section class="container-prose pt-16 pb-12">
    <div class="reveal mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
      <h2 class="section-heading !mb-0">Orpheus</h2>
      <span class="pill pill-gold">Active</span>
    </div>

    <div class="reveal card overflow-hidden">
      <div class="h-2.5 bg-gradient-to-r from-[#0F2A4A] via-[#1E4E7A] to-[#4A90D9]"></div>
      <div class="p-6 md:p-8">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-1 flex-wrap gap-2">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-ink)]" style="font-family: var(--font-serif);">Mesa-Optimization Probe</h3>
          <span class="text-xs font-mono text-[var(--color-faint)] whitespace-nowrap">Apr 2026 → Present</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-2 flex-wrap mb-5 mt-3">
          <span class="pill pill-accent">PyTorch</span>
          <span class="pill pill-accent">TransformerLens</span>
          <span class="pill pill-accent">Mechanistic Interpretability</span>
          <span class="pill pill-accent">Activation Patching</span>
        </div>

        <div class="callout-finding mb-6">
          <span class="tag">Research question</span>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-ink)] leading-relaxed italic" style="font-family: var(--font-serif);">
            Do small transformers trained on in-context learning tasks implement gradient-descent-like optimization internally during their forward pass? If so, where in the network does this emerge, and what computational signatures distinguish a mesa-optimizer from a lookup table?
          </p>
        </div>

        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-muted)] leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Training small transformers (1–4 layers) on synthetic in-context linear regression, then using mechanistic interpretability to reverse-engineer the algorithms they learn. The goal is to identify whether the internal computation resembles an optimization process — gradient descent on an implicit loss — rather than pattern matching or memorization.
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
          <a href="/projects/orpheus" class="btn-primary magnetic !py-2 !px-5 !text-xs">
            Full case study
            <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6"/></svg>
          </a>
          <a href="https://github.com/Aryanharitsa" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-ghost magnetic !py-2 !px-5 !text-xs">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 0C5.37 0 0 5.37 0 12c0 5.31 3.435 9.795 8.205 11.385.6.105.825-.255.825-.57 0-.285-.015-1.23-.015-2.235-3.015.555-3.795-.735-4.035-1.41-.135-.345-.72-1.41-1.23-1.695-.42-.225-1.02-.78-.015-.795.945-.015 1.62.87 1.845 1.23 1.08 1.815 2.805 1.305 3.495.99.105-.78.42-1.305.765-1.605-2.67-.3-5.46-1.335-5.46-5.925 0-1.305.465-2.385 1.23-3.225-.12-.3-.54-1.53.12-3.18 0 0 1.005-.315 3.3 1.23.96-.27 1.98-.405 3-.405s2.04.135 3 .405c2.295-1.56 3.3-1.23 3.3-1.23.66 1.65.24 2.88.12 3.18.765.84 1.23 1.905 1.23 3.225 0 4.605-2.805 5.625-5.475 5.925.435.375.81 1.095.81 2.22 0 1.605-.015 2.895-.015 3.3 0 .315.225.69.825.57A12.02 12.02 0 0024 12c0-6.63-5.37-12-12-12z"/></svg>
            GitHub
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ VITRUVIUS ============ -->
  <section class="container-prose pb-12">
    <div class="reveal mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
      <h2 class="section-heading !mb-0">Vitruvius</h2>
      <span class="pill pill-gold">v0.8.0 · 90%</span>
    </div>

    <div class="reveal card overflow-hidden">
      <div class="h-2.5 bg-gradient-to-r from-[#B4892A] via-[#1E4E7A] to-[#0F2A4A]"></div>
      <div class="p-6 md:p-8">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-1 flex-wrap gap-2">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-ink)]" style="font-family: var(--font-serif);">Encoder Archaeology</h3>
          <span class="text-xs font-mono text-[var(--color-faint)] whitespace-nowrap">Apr 2026 → Phase 8 landed</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-2 flex-wrap mb-5 mt-3">
          <span class="pill pill-accent">BEIR</span>
          <span class="pill pill-accent">MS MARCO</span>
          <span class="pill pill-accent">Mamba</span>
          <span class="pill pill-accent">LSTM · CNN</span>
          <span class="pill pill-accent">FAISS</span>
          <span class="pill pill-accent">pytrec_eval</span>
        </div>

        <div class="callout-finding mb-6">
          <span class="tag">Research question</span>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-ink)] leading-relaxed italic" style="font-family: var(--font-serif);">
            Are bidirectional transformer encoders truly optimal for dense retrieval, or can alternative architectures (SSMs, recurrent models, long-convolution models) achieve comparable quality at lower latency? Where specifically is the transformer's full bidirectional attention earning its cost versus being wasted compute?
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Latest findings block -->
        <p class="section-label mb-3">Latest findings · Phase 5 → 8</p>
        <div class="space-y-3 mb-6">
          <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
            <span class="w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-gold)] text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">1</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-muted)] leading-relaxed"><strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">Pareto frontier resolved.</strong> Averaged across the 3 BEIR subsets, the optimal subset is <code>gte-small</code>, <code>minilm-l6-v2</code>, <code>lstm-retriever</code>, <code>conv-retriever</code>. Mamba and BERT-base are both dominated.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
            <span class="w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-gold)] text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">2</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-muted)] leading-relaxed"><strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">LSTM is the most position-tolerant.</strong> Doc-shuffle sensitivity 0.166 — the lowest of all four families. A 6.4M-parameter BiLSTM retains 83% of retrieval quality on shuffled documents.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
            <span class="w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-gold)] text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">3</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-muted)] leading-relaxed"><strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">Most attention heads are prunable zero-shot.</strong> Cumulative pruning of MiniLM / BERT / GTE: the majority of heads can be zeroed at &lt;5% nDCG@10 drop without retraining.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
            <span class="w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-gold)] text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">4</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-muted)] leading-relaxed"><strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">The deployment myth dies.</strong> "Route-hard-queries-to-big-model" does not hold: 127 unique transformer wins vs 19 from-scratch unique wins across 3 datasets.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Encoder family grid -->
        <p class="section-label mb-3">Architecture families under study</p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-2 mb-6">
          <div class="border border-[var(--color-rule)] rounded-md p-3 text-center bg-[var(--color-surface)]">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold" style="font-family: var(--font-serif); color: var(--color-accent);">Transformer</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-faint)] mt-0.5">MiniLM · BERT · GTE</p>
          </div>
          <div class="border border-[var(--color-rule)] rounded-md p-3 text-center bg-[var(--color-surface)]">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold" style="font-family: var(--font-serif); color: var(--color-accent);">Recurrent</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-faint)] mt-0.5">BiLSTM (from-scratch)</p>
          </div>
          <div class="border border-[var(--color-rule)] rounded-md p-3 text-center bg-[var(--color-surface)]">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold" style="font-family: var(--font-serif); color: var(--color-accent);">Convolutional</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-faint)] mt-0.5">1D CNN (k = 3/5/7)</p>
          </div>
          <div class="border border-[var(--color-rule)] rounded-md p-3 text-center bg-[var(--color-surface)]">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold" style="font-family: var(--font-serif); color: var(--color-accent);">State-Space</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-faint)] mt-0.5">Mamba2 (from-scratch)</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
          <a href="/projects/vitruvius" class="btn-primary magnetic !py-2 !px-5 !text-xs">
            Full case study
            <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6"/></svg>
          </a>
          <a href="https://github.com/Aryanharitsa" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-ghost magnetic !py-2 !px-5 !text-xs">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 0C5.37 0 0 5.37 0 12c0 5.31 3.435 9.795 8.205 11.385.6.105.825-.255.825-.57 0-.285-.015-1.23-.015-2.235-3.015.555-3.795-.735-4.035-1.41-.135-.345-.72-1.41-1.23-1.695-.42-.225-1.02-.78-.015-.795.945-.015 1.62.87 1.845 1.23 1.08 1.815 2.805 1.305 3.495.99.105-.78.42-1.305.765-1.605-2.67-.3-5.46-1.335-5.46-5.925 0-1.305.465-2.385 1.23-3.225-.12-.3-.54-1.53.12-3.18 0 0 1.005-.315 3.3 1.23.96-.27 1.98-.405 3-.405s2.04.135 3 .405c2.295-1.56 3.3-1.23 3.3-1.23.66 1.65.24 2.88.12 3.18.765.84 1.23 1.905 1.23 3.225 0 4.605-2.805 5.625-5.475 5.925.435.375.81 1.095.81 2.22 0 1.605-.015 2.895-.015 3.3 0 .315.225.69.825.57A12.02 12.02 0 0024 12c0-6.63-5.37-12-12-12z"/></svg>
            GitHub
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="container-prose"><div class="h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-[var(--color-accent)]/15 to-transparent"></div></div>

  <!-- ============ PAPERS ============ -->
  <section class="container-prose pt-16 pb-20">
    <div class="reveal mb-6">
      <h2 class="section-heading">Papers</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="stagger grid gap-6">
      <div class="reveal card shimmer-border overflow-hidden">
        <div class="h-2 bg-gradient-to-r from-[#0F2A4A] to-[#4A90D9]"></div>
        <div class="p-6">
          <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4 mb-2 flex-wrap">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--color-ink)]" style="font-family: var(--font-serif);">TITAN: Trustworthy Identity Tokenization and Attestation Network</h3>
            <span class="pill pill-amber whitespace-nowrap">Submitted</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs font-mono text-[var(--color-faint)] mb-3">Submitted to SeCrypt 2026</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-muted)] leading-relaxed mb-4">
            End-to-end identity verification: AI-powered document forensics, zero-knowledge proofs for private on-chain attestation, and GNN-based transaction graph analysis for anti-money laundering. KYC compliance without exposing raw identity documents to verifiers.
          </p>
          <div class="flex gap-2 flex-wrap">
            <span class="pill pill-accent">ZK Proofs</span>
            <span class="pill pill-accent">Circom</span>
            <span class="pill pill-accent">GNN</span>
            <span class="pill pill-accent">KYC/AML</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="reveal card shimmer-border overflow-hidden">
        <div class="h-2 bg-gradient-to-r from-[#4A90D9] to-[#7AB8F5]"></div>
        <div class="p-6">
          <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4 mb-2 flex-wrap">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--color-ink)]" style="font-family: var(--font-serif);">Emergent Features in Large Language Models</h3>
            <span class="pill pill-accent whitespace-nowrap">Working draft</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs font-mono text-[var(--color-faint)] mb-3">In progress</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-muted)] leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Investigating feature emergence patterns in LLMs across scale. How capabilities appear discontinuously, and what mechanistic signatures precede emergent behavior. Connecting Orpheus's findings on in-context optimization to broader questions about what large models learn to compute.
          </p>
          <div class="flex gap-2 flex-wrap">
            <span class="pill pill-accent">LLMs</span>
            <span class="pill pill-accent">Emergence</span>
            <span class="pill pill-accent">Interpretability</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="reveal card shimmer-border overflow-hidden">
        <div class="h-2 bg-gradient-to-r from-[#B4892A] to-[#8A6414]"></div>
        <div class="p-6">
          <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4 mb-2 flex-wrap">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--color-ink)]" style="font-family: var(--font-serif);">Vitruvius — Technical Note</h3>
            <span class="pill pill-gold whitespace-nowrap">Phase 9 · in progress</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs font-mono text-[var(--color-faint)] mb-3">5–7 pages · arXiv-ready</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-muted)] leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Short, opinionated technical note synthesizing the Vitruvius sweep. What changed our minds about the transformer's inductive bias for retrieval, and exactly where we were wrong.
          </p>
          <div class="flex gap-2 flex-wrap">
            <span class="pill pill-accent">Dense Retrieval</span>
            <span class="pill pill-accent">Pareto</span>
            <span class="pill pill-accent">Architectures</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>
